title: For Sale:  1st Gen Colt Single Action Army Artillery - PENNY
postcontent: Up for sale is an original and 100%  shipped and marked Colt single action army, .45 caliber, former 7-1/2" cavalry revolver, shortened to 5-1/2" per request of the US government. These specially altered US government revolvers are most commonly referred to as "Artillery" models. No special care was taken in preserving the matching assembly and serial numbers of these refinished and modified pistols and they were reworked in relatively large numbers. These single actions are very interesting to debunk as nearly every part came from a different US cavalry gun from a different era. This particular gun has a frame with the serial number 120291 (c.1887), trigger guard marked with the serial number 96034 (c.1883), and a back strap with the serial number 82019 (c.1882). The frame bears the inspection mark of "D.F.C" David F. Clark. The cylinder is Marked with the serial number "6339" and is also marked "D.F.C". The trigger guard is marked with a "G" and the back strap has no visible inspector marking. The barrel is correctly double proofed and is marked with "2277" and the inspector mark "R.A.C." Rinaldo A. Carr. The grip has both original cartouches. They are weak. The LH is the better of the two with the 1901 date still be readable. This artillery single action is no doubt an original example with all original parts and I guarantee the authenticity. The condition is very good. The frame has been cleaned up some but still has some original case color in protected areas. The barrel is mostly a lightly cleaned silver patina. The guard and ejector housing actually still have some bright original bluing. The grip is free from cracks or major damage. Bore is near mint with strong rifling. Mechanically excellent. A great original and early single action artillery, shipping is also available.
